Four people have been taken to hospital after a crash in Devon, Devon and Cornwall Police say.The incident happened on the A386 between Mary Tavy and Lydford at about 19:15 BST on Sunday.The incident involved a white Citroen Dispatch van and a grey and black Renault Captur.A police spokesperson said two women aged 29 and 58, who were both in the Renault, suffered "serious injuries".
A second female passenger in the same car sustained minor injuries, as did the male driver of the Citroen.The road was closed while emergency services dealt with the scene. It was reopened at about 07.40 on Monday, officers said. 
